headline: DGX Q1 Earnings Call: Acquisitions, Advanced Diagnostics, and Operational Initiatives Drive Growth
summary: Healthcare diagnostics company Quest Diagnostics (NYSE:DGX) reported Q1 CY2025 results exceeding the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 12.1% year on year to $2.65 billion. The company expects the full year’s revenue to be around $10.78 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.21 per share was 2.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
